  m_Name: Forepaw_Digit4_Phalanx_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Forepaw_Digit4_Phalanx_L
  partName: Forepaw Digit4 Phalanx Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left forepaw digit four phalanx is a skeletal component of the fourth toe
    located within the canine left forepaw. This structure supports controlled movement
    of the digit while contributing to balance, stability, and proper weight distribution
    during locomotion.
  - Muscles, tendons, and ligaments attached to the phalanx enable coordinated flexion
    and extension necessary for accurate paw placement and traction. The fourth digit
    also assists with shock absorption and maintenance of stable ground contact during
    walking and running activities.
